<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10856&amp;p=123346#p123346"><![CDATA[
Is this SNES specific? I imagine that NES games are limited in the kinds of compression they use because of the little amount of RAM (when they didn't have extra RAM in the cart). A lot of them didn't even need graphics compression because they use CHR-ROM.<br /><br />But no matter the console, storage space always becomes cheaper later in its life, and effects that need tons of uncompressed data in order to be performed in realtime start to become tempting to developers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jan 05, 2014 2:17 pm</p><hr />
